<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 4:00PM EDT  by NWS Wakefield</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL AFFECT SOUTHERN MECKLENBURG COUNTY...
At 400 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Clarksville, or
14 miles east of Virgilina, moving east at 40 mph.
Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail are possible with this
storm.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southern
Mecklenburg County, including the following locations... Richardson,
Beechwood, Bracey, Keats, John H Kerr Dam, Eppes Fork, John H Kerr
Reservoir, Palmer Springs and Lake Gaston.</description>
